Wash and dry produce.

Roughly chop half the @sliced dill pickle{1%unit}. Halve @potato buns{2}; toast until golden brown. Thinly slice @tomato{1%unit} into rounds.

In a small #bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, chopped pickle, and as much @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like.

Pat @fully cooked chicken breasts{8.6%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

In a medium microwave-safe bowl, combine chicken, half the @BBQ seasoning{1%tablespoon}, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Spread top and bottom buns with spicy mayo. Fill buns with chicken, tomato, and sliced pickle. Divide sandwiches between plates and serve.